wikipedia_page.main: Shirley Cawley (born 26 April 1932) is a former British athlete who won the bronze medal in the long jump at the 1952 Summer Olympics held in Helsinki, Finland. She was born in Croydon and ran for the Croydon Harriers, she later married and became Shirley Berry.
